The Independent Petroleum Marketers Association Of Nigeria (IPMAN) has congratulated President Muhammadu Buhari and Nigerians on the occasion of the country’s 60th Independence anniversary and also prayed for peace and unity in the nation. The National President, IPMAN, Alhaji Sanusi Abdu Fari, disclosed this in a statement made available to newsmen yesterday in Abuja. Fari said, “the National Executive Committee (NEC) of IPMAN congratulates President Muhammadu Buhari and the good people of Nigeria on this joyous occasion of the celebration of our Independence. “The IPMAN leadership at the BOT, National, Zonal, Unit levels and members nationwide are happy to be associated with this diamond celebration. “It is our prayers that God Almighty will continue to grant us the grace for a united and peaceful nation, Nigeria. “IPMAN shall continue to partner with NARTO, NUPENG and Petroleum Tanker Drivers(PTD) in contributing her quota towards ensuring uninterrupted supply and distribution of Petroleum Products across the country.” 